def pnm.input.inputManager.InputManager.__setupKeyboard (   self,
  keyboardConfig = "keyboard.cfg" 
) [private]

Load a keyboard map.

Keyboard maps are stored using the ogre config file, with a slight extention.

example:

-----------------------------------
[Global]
r-LSHIFT+ESCAPE=exit
p-SPACE=jumpLeft
h-CONTROL+Z=run
-----------------------------------

The line 1 declares the map name. Each of the following lines declares a new key combo input untill the next map name. Each combo has three parts:

[type]-[key]=[event]

type; p - pressed, h - hold, r - released
key; keys, using the OIS names (minus "KC_"), joined with "+". In the case of CONTROL and SHIFT, the combo is replaced with two seperate combos with both left and right keys in.
event; the event name passed to pnm.events.eventManager.EventManager.hook

Note: Each combo can only contain one of each keys.

Parameters:
keyboardConfig - Keyboard config file name
